# Project-wide shellcheck config.
#
# These suppressions are scoped to skill code-block snippets in
# `.claude/commands/nase/*.md` (extracted by `.github/workflows/validate.yml`),
# where placeholders like `{repo}` and `<owner>/<repo>` make several rules noisy
# without indicating real bugs. They also apply to `tests/` and `.claude/hooks/`
# scripts run with `shellcheck -S warning`; if a rule starts catching real bugs
# there, scope it tighter via inline `# shellcheck disable=...` directives.
#
# SC2148 — no shebang (snippets aren't standalone scripts)
# SC2154 — placeholder variables like {repo}/{slug}
# SC1091 — `source` paths in illustrative examples
# SC2034 — variables defined for example clarity but unused
# SC2016 — single-quoted `$var` in jq filters and similar literals
# SC2260 — `<owner>` placeholder reads as redirection
# SC2261 — same family

disable=SC2148,SC2154,SC1091,SC2034,SC2016,SC2260,SC2261
